title.rendered: Brisbane vs Sydney, Australian T20 League 2022: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Brisbane: Max Bryant, Colin Munro, Matt Renshaw, Sam Billings, Jimmy Peirson (c & wk), Ross Whiteley, Michael Neser, Xavier Bartlett, Mark Steketee, Matthew Kuhnemann, Mitchell Swepson

Sydney: Alex Hales, Matthew Gilkes (wk), Rilee Rossouw, Oliver Davies, Daniel Sams, Alex Ross, Nathan McAndrew, Chris Green (c), Gurinder Sandhu, Brendan Doggett, Usman Qadir

Pitch Report

Venue: Carrara Oval, Queensland

1st innings average score: 130

2nd innings average score: 121

Type: Even battle between the bat and ball.

Weather: Slightly cloudy.

Wins

Batting 1st: 50%

Batting 2nd: 50%

Fantasy Tips of the Day

With 159 runs, Alex Hales is the third-highest run-scorer of the series. He has provided bonus fantasy points for two fifties, a strike rate of 140, and 23 boundaries.

Be it with the new or old ball, Daniel Sams has been consistently amongst wickets, thanks to his change-in-pace deliveries. His 9 wickets have come at a strike rate of 12.

All in all, both teams have been struggling to play as a unit and hence are stuttering in the points table. That being said, Sydney boast of a balance unit, producing fantasy points in all the departments.
